data.text:
You might sometimes find him “Under the sea," but this time Cortez the Green Turtle is peeking out from “Under the plane!" 
⁠
Great 📸 catch from Frontier Pilot, Ethan H. ⁠
⁠
Green with envy? Catch Cortez on your next flight on Frontier: https://t.co/kmvcTDnvYX https://t.co/l3MEGM37Jy

Hey everyone! Welcome "Watson the Key Deer" to our fleet! 

This endangered deer is native to the Everglades and the Florida Keys in South Florida. 

Watson is deer to our heart! We hope you see him on your next flight on Frontier! https://t.co/ALs49Ap1jZ https://t.co/4iTw4v2bQ2

Flight Crew 2126 helped Ashton ring in his 5th birthday, singing, "Happy Birthday," over the microphone and a visit to the Captain's chair! 

Not only was it his birthday, it was his very first flight! Cheers to this future Pilot! ❤️✈️ https://t.co/5a6ENNVwNs

The Cheyenne Inflight Training team recently spent the day volunteering with Needs Inc, a nonprofit that provides food, clothing, household items and other services to residents in the
Laramie County area. Grateful for opportunity to serve in the community! https://t.co/vdJBVk9ig8
We will never forget. You are always in our hearts and our thoughts. ✈️❤️ https://t.co/INQpwnUByN
